-- Rays Outfielder Wil Myers Chosen American League Rookie of Year
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2013-11-11T23:23:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-11/rays-outfielder-wil-myers-chosen-american-league-rookie-of-year.html
Tampa Bay outfielder Wil Myers was
selected today as the  American League ’s top rookie, becoming the
third Rays player in the last six seasons to win the award.  Myers finished ahead of Rays pitcher Chris Archer and
Detroit Tigers shortstop Jose Iglesias in voting conducted by
the Baseball Writers’ Association of America.  In the National League, the three finalists for Rookie of
the Year are Miami Marlins pitcher Jose Fernandez, Los
Angeles Dodgers outfielder Yasiel Puig and St. Louis Cardinals
pitcher Shelby Miller.  The rest of Major League Baseball’s top awards -- including
Most Valuable Player and Manager of the Year -- will be
announced later this week.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  